page.title: 10WILDLIFE.
page.content: There are herds of Red Deer which rarely come down near houses or farms, but can be seen on the hills. In the hills you can find Wildcat and foxes and in the wooded areas the Roe Deer There are hares_ white mountain ones and the more common grey hare. Rabbits which are very numerous are found everywhere. Of these the Roe Deer,fox,hares, and rabbits are no friend of the farmer!. Grouse are plentiful in the hills, the pheasant and partridge being bred by the gamekeepers .There are weasals stoats Red squirrels and moles. Ospreys have been sighted in this area, also a few buzzard, hawks kestrels and capercaillies. Large flocks of oystercatchers and lapwing arrive in spring. Many other small birds nest here including the gray wagtail.
